President Obama has declared an emergency in Massachusetts and ordered federal aid to help with the severe storm that occurred from October 29-30, 2011. The Department of Homeland Security, specifically the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA), will coordinate disaster relief efforts in the affected counties. FEMA is authorized to provide necessary equipment and resources to alleviate the impacts of the emergency, with 75 percent federal funding for emergency protective measures. Mark H. Landry has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk.